    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-04-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-04-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="324"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d324">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Adams</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 916.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-04-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 22, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have your despatch of April 8, No. 653, which
                    relates to the proceedings at Mauritius, in the matter of the cargo of the Sea
                    Bride. It will be well, I think, to defer a representation on that subject until
                    a season more propitious than the present one.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic"
                            >&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
